H0.text: The heart pumps the blood in the body.

H1.text: Systolic pressure pumps the blood in the body.

H2.text: Respiratory is what the blood in the body is pumped with.

H3.text: Lung is what the blood in the body is pumped with.

A4.text: The heart pumps blood with a rhythm determined by a group of pacemaker cells in the sinoatrial node.

A5.text: The heart is a muscular organ found in humans and other animals. This organ pumps blood through the blood vessels.
